website_summaries.verdict: The Definitive Technology Symphony 1 is a good-looking wireless headphone pair that delivers solid audio performance and noise cancellation.
pros: Powerful audio performance with rich bass and a focus on clarity in the higher frequencies
Active noise cancellation and wireless audio
Can be used passively with included audio cable
cons: Audio can distort when using cable instead of wireless connection

customer_reviews.title: The Def Tech Symphony 1 is a great pair of noise cancelling headphones
customer_reviews.text: The Def Tech Symphony 1 is a great pair of noise cancelling headphones, though not the best I tried, these are, by far, the best I've owned. They are pretty well balanced, all the way from the rich accurate bass to the controlled highs. When ANC is on, it lowers the clarity of music by a little bit, barely noticeable, but as far as sound dampening (passively and actively) these headphones do a very good job. These headphones will transport you from a loud environment to a concert hall.
customer_reviews.author: Lauro

customer_reviews.title: Excellent Headphones, at Home or on a Plane.
customer_reviews.text: I have a set of Bose noise reduction headphones. Their noise reduction is very good, but their music was biases towards the midrange. The Symphony 1's were fabulous. You are in the middle of the music and you can clearly hear the highs and lows as the artists intended. The music is almost as good as hearing it live. The noise reduction is every bit as good as the Bose. I wear these while in small turboprop planes. I can barely hear the plane. The prop noise and wind noise is gone. They are worth every penny.
customer_reviews.author: R. W. Taylor

customer_reviews.title: Lacks punch or excitement.  Build quality is good.  Bulky but comfortable.
customer_reviews.text: Good quality headphones. They fit my large head comfortably. I like that you can use a USB cable to both charge and carry the digital audio signal from a PC at the same time, which should give better audio fidelity than Bluetooth. Sound quality is disappointing if you're expecting enhanced bass and highs that are typical of Bose and Beats headphones. Had I been able to audition these before purchasing, I would not have bought them. If you want accurate sound, these are a good choice. Also, the ANC works well in my office environment. Really well actually.
customer_reviews.author: AmznCust

customer_reviews.title: These are so AWESOME! I own Definitive home theater speakers as well
customer_reviews.text: Are you kidding me? These are so AWESOME! I own Definitive home theater speakers as well, so knew I would get a quality product for the price. Not sure why some of these other folks were unhappy as I've owned a TON of headsets and nothing sounds this amazing.
customer_reviews.author: Mike Morgan

customer_reviews.title: Sound stage and noise cancellation works perfectly.
customer_reviews.text: I read many reviews about the symphony 1 and sort of got mixed reviews. This is my second day trying the headphone in my noisy wind tunnel office. It really blocks all that noise and the music sounds very good. With the anc I don't have to crank the volume pass 30% and still get a very detail sound from low to high notes. The noise cancellation works perfectly for me. I tried the qc35 and qc30 as well and the noise cancellation gave me a little headache with the excessive high pitch. The symphony balance that out by not completely blocking all the noise. The sound stage is perfect.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: I am very happy with my new Symphony 1 headphones
customer_reviews.text: I am very happy with my new Symphony 1 headphones. They fit my head and my ears. I've worn them while cleaning and they haven't fallen off my head. They fill my ears with great sound - like I'm sitting in a room with surround sound. My KEF M500, which I love, are a rich full sound, but not wireless. The Symphony 1 have a nice bass and the sound is crisp and clear. I've got the best of both worlds. I had no problem setting up or using. 1 tip - to turn on or off, just push the button and release - do not hold any length of time.
customer_reviews.author: P. Bahr

customer_reviews.title: Great sound if it doesn't lock up
customer_reviews.text: Excellent sound when the headphones do not freeze up after recharge. This has happened several times now and still only about 8 months old so will be returning. Update: spoke to Chet in tech support. If the headphones freeze, simply press & release both ANC & Vol up buttons to reset. Chet said its usually rare but if frequent resets are required to call back for further troubleshooting. Working now, so unless anything changes I do recommend these headphones due to the super quality sound output.
customer_reviews.author: scott howard

customer_reviews.title: The ear cup is perfect! I can wear them all day
customer_reviews.text: I bought Sennheiser Momentum 2.0 wireless about a month ago and have been using it at work which means very long wearing time. The ear cup is too small. My ears hurt after about 30min or so. Bought this Definitive Technology Symphony 1 headphone last week. The ear cup is perfect! I can wear them all day. The Bluetooth connection to my PC seems more simple and robust than Sennheiser. Sound quality wise, Sennheiser is a little better in terms of clarity and sound stage. But for casual listening at work, DT Symphony 1 is adequate.
customer_reviews.author: HIFI enthusiast

customer_reviews.title: They're ok
customer_reviews.text: Ehh, I wanted to like these, but was never too thrilled with them. PROS: Good sound quality Solid construction Decent battery life CONS: Glitchy bluetooth Mediocre comfort
customer_reviews.author: Todd M

customer_reviews.title: Good head phones with noise cancellation but deceptive list price.
customer_reviews.text: Note this is the Symphony 1 Executive headphones. List price by another source on Amazon as $199 but sold for $149. Battery life is 10 hours with noise canceling on, not 15hours. The sound is very good and the noise canceling is effective. They are a good buy at $149.
customer_reviews.author: ragweed

customer_reviews.title: 5 star sound...comfort/design not so much
customer_reviews.text: Incredible sound, but bulky and not as comfortable as some other highly rated headphones. Also have a tendency to lock up after charging, requiring a full reset...which can get annoying. But if you care primarily about sound quality, these are amazing.
customer_reviews.author: OperaMan

customer_reviews.title: Beautiful sounding bluetooth headphones
customer_reviews.text: Excellent sound especially when used in the wired or DAC modes with ANC and power on. Sounds very good in wireless/bluetooth mode as well just not as amazing as the wired perfomance. Noise cancellation is pretty good when not actively listening to something and is next to perfect when you have music playing. I used this on the DC metro and didn't hear anything outside of my music the entire time. The headset is very comfortable with large earcups that enclose the entire ear and do a pretty good job passively isolating noise on their own.
customer_reviews.author: Abraham

customer_reviews.title: I,am 100% Happy with my Defintive Technogy

The soundstage is there wired or bluetooth, I have used a lot of headphones in search of the perfect headphones, and finally my search is over for now. It you give them some break in time and getting used to the quality of these headphones you will realize they are great pair of CANS....

customer_reviews.title: Great all around headphones.
customer_reviews.text: These have crystal clear sound. The noise cancellation works great. You hear just enough to notice your surroundings. Not a base heavy headphone but just the right mix for me.

customer_reviews.title: A- Effort from Def Tech
customer_reviews.text: Good sound over USB and BT, not so great with the 2.5mm (they sound a bit weaker, almost "unamped"). They look fantastic, and are pretty comfortable (if a bit tight at first). The ANC mode drowns out all of the sound in my office, and most of the sound on a plane (not quite as good as Bose QCs), and the sound quality is much better than the QCs.

customer_reviews.title: Love them
customer_reviews.text: I like to read reviews before a purchase. Mainly the negative comments. I was a little concerned that the headphones wouldn't fit my big head. I couldn't find a place that carried them in stock to test the fit. For $150, I took a chance. Glad I did. Fit my big head perfectly. Sound awesome, better than my Bose qc25. And the Bluetooth works about 75 feet away. Perfect!
customer_reviews.author: dave burtchell

customer_reviews.title: A winner!!!! Great for the price.
customer_reviews.text: WOW...WOW...WOW!!! Incredible sound. If you are an audiophile you will love the way all music is reproduced. FLAC or MP3 etc. sounds very spacious and great tonality. Bright highs, excellent mids, and good base. Very loud. so you will not have any issue with that. Bluetooth connectivity is superb. Light weight and comfortable. Great looking.

customer_reviews.author: Jack

customer_reviews.title: Sound Great
customer_reviews.text: The sound is amazing. They are well built and comfortable. The sound is well balanced with good bottom end and very clean and natural mids and highs. It is the first pair of headphones that I have had with active noise canceling, so I don’t have anything to compare with, but it seems to work well. They were easy to pair with my phone and I have not had any firmware glitches that others have reported. They did feel a little heavy after a 4 hour flight, but that is trying to find an issue with these. I get 10-12 hours of use per charge. They’re well priced, sound great and I am glad that I bought these headphones.
customer_reviews.author: C. Doris

customer_reviews.title: Awesome wireless noise cancelling headphones with some minor drawbacks
customer_reviews.text: Awesome sounding headphones. Has solid not boomy bass and clean highs. Can break up a bit in the higher registers when pushed. Sounds best with the ANC on. Connects easily and haven't had any issues with dropping. Comfortable earpieces but headband can become uncomfortable with extensive wearing. Excellent battery life. Carry case is large but protects them very well. Doesn't fold to a compact size to pack.

customer_reviews.title: Quality Headphones
customer_reviews.text: These are excellent head phones. I love not having to be attached to a wire although it ain't that bad. The pads aren't quite as soft as Bose but I can live with that also. Sound quality is great.

customer_reviews.title: Great, but bulky

customer_reviews.title: Buggy Bluetooth but Incredible Sound with FLAC files.
customer_reviews.text: While it's undoubtable that the sound quality on these headphones is incredible (this should be in BOLD), especially when playing FLAC files, the Bluetooth connectivity is very fiddly even using the latest OSX 10.10.4. In comparison the Bose Soundlink mini connects perfectly via Bluetooth every time. Unfortunately, the Symphony 1 struggles to connect to Bluetooth (and drop outs) plus turning on the ANC (noise cancellation) is problematic. For the price I would have expected greater stability.

customer_reviews.title: Disappointing sound quality.
customer_reviews.text: I didn't think these were better than the Shure 850s I own. The sound is just not that rich. I took a chance as Def Tech makes amazing tower speakers. These are light and comfy. The Bluetooth works well. USB sounds better than 3.5 stereo plug. Purchase them if you want decent bluetooth headphones. If you want amazing sound, look elsewhere.

customer_reviews.title: DO-NOT-BUY These Headphones.  Waste of $.  Buy Bose or another company with a decent warranty
customer_reviews.text: An absolute DO-NOT-BUY. I've had these headphones for 3 months now and already need to get them replaced. The battery already densest last more than two hours without needing to be charged. The headphones periodically freeze with the power on and do not reset until they run out of battery (Very frustrating). The Bluetooth cuts out and doesn't work well. The "noise canceling" part hardly cancels out noise. They make great music, but are very crappy quality. They also do not have a competitive warranty to offer... Buy bose or a bigger company with a better warranty and quality of headphones
customer_reviews.author: Traveler

customer_reviews.title: Bluetooth connectivity is poor.
customer_reviews.text: These are going back. Bluetooth cut out about every minute on an iPhone 7 Plus. They were fully charged, and we tried them with two different phones, same result. They are comfortable, but a bit bulky and heavy. Even if Bluetooth was rock solid, I think we'd return them due to the weight.
customer_reviews.author: Mike

customer_reviews.title: Paid for new item, and I received an used item.
customer_reviews.text: I purchased a new set of headphones, and I received a used pair of headphones. The box was reaped with clear square tape. The original tape is round. The wire were coiled with a fold in the middle.

customer_reviews.title: A+ design, C- functionality
customer_reviews.text: So many reasons why I didn't like these wireless premium headphones. The Bluetooth connection was terrible and the sound quality was awful. The packaging and design were first rate, go figure. I sent them back.

I think these are defective.

customer_reviews.title: John Legend Recommended in WSJ Travel
customer_reviews.text: Bought it because of WSJ Travel article recommended by John Legend. Dissapointing look, quality, finish and touch in person. Disappointing sound quality. Electronics and switches are high quality. Heavy. I also own Beats and Bose. Recommend QC Bose 25.

product_meta.title: Definitive Technology Symphony 1 Over-Ear Bluetooth Wireless Headphones - Black
product_meta.description:
Richly Detailed, Hi–Fi Listening Richly detailed full fidelity deep bass delivers a truly exhilarating audiophile performance. Every note precisely rendered by 50mm full–frequency range drivers with an exceptionally broad soundstage. The headphones are constructed of lightweight aluminum for hours of comfortable listening further feeding your sound obsession.

Unencumbered listening experience Enjoy an unencumbered listening experience free from distracting connecting cables with Bluetooth wireless technology. With a range of over 30', you can leave your device on the desk or table while you listen to your favorite playlist the next room over. A rechargeable battery will continue to keep your music pouring from earcup to eardrum for up to 15 hours.

Active Noise Canceling Each earcup forms a positive over–ear seal to dampen external distracting noises, and dual–mode active noise canceling. Symphony 1 automatically senses background noises and adjusts cancellaiton levels accordingly. Outstanding voice reception when using a smartphone allows you to pause the music, answer your call and go right back to your the point in the track where you left off.

Earcup Controls Easily control and adjust volume, play controls, bluetooth on/off, noise cancelling on/off, power on/off all from the side of the earcup. Located conveniently on the right earcup, you can make all the necessary changes you need without having to remove Symphony headphones from your ears.
feature_bullets: Immerse yourself in precision crafted, audiophile grade sound wherever you are with the Definitive Technology Symphony 1 executive Bluetooth headphones; Connectivity Technology: Wireless
50 millimeter drivers offer detailed, full fidelity highs and mids and rich, deep bass for a big, natural soundstage
Convenient Bluetooth connectivity for wireless listening and phone calls
Closed back, over ear design seals out external sound while active noise cancellation (ANC) technology dramatically reduces ambient noise
Built in rechargeable battery lasts up to 15 hours with noise cancellation on
